experiments_run.name: Random restart
experiments_run.notes: Random placement cannot achieve tight packing. Local search too weak.

experiments_run.name: Lattice placement (hexagonal + square)
experiments_run.notes: Simple lattice patterns cannot match baseline's interlocking structure.

conclusion: Random restart and lattice approaches cannot match the baseline. The baseline uses sophisticated interlocking patterns that simple algorithms cannot replicate. The 20-35% gap from theoretical minimum suggests improvement IS possible, but requires advanced algorithms (C++ SA with millions of iterations, or novel packing algorithms).
